n a branch or\ninside `meta:local:*`.\n\nA good first command shape is:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture \\\n  --agent codex \\\n  --transcript-path <path> \\\n  --target project\n```\n\n## Design Bias\n\nPrefer safety and auditability over clever discovery. It is better for the POC\nto capture nothing unless given an exact transcript than to accidentally capture\nthe wrong or private session.\n\n## Docum\n[TRUNCATED]\nter GitMeta exchange and resume\n  UX are designed\n- colleague/reviewer browsing through a future GitButler web view that can show\n  the prompts, responses, tool activity, and prompting quality behind a branch\n  or pull request\n\nThose use cases require project-scoped sessions plus future relationship keys.\nThey do not require branch inference in the POC.\n\n## Later Goals\n\n- Capture the current or recent AI coding session without an explicit path.\n- Prefer deterministic hook-style capture when an agent can provide an exact\n  transcript path or session id.\n- Search known agent locations, filtered by repository, when no exact input is\n  available.\n- Add Cursor only after Codex and Claude establish the shared shape. Cursor needs\n  a separate design pass because its normal chat history is local SQLite and its\n  official portable format is Markdown export.\n- Add GitMeta serialize/fetch/push/sync behavior only after privacy and product\n  behavior are explicit.\n\nAgent-specific discovery notes live in [Capture Workflow](capture-workflow.md).\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- No automatic background capture in the first milestone.\n- No heuristic session discovery in the first milestone.\n- No GitMeta serialization, push, fetch, or sync in the first milestone.\n- No branch, commit, change-id, or pull request inference in the first milestone.\n- No machine-wide scraping of AI tool storage.\n- No dependency on provider-specific crates such as `but-claude`.\n- No `meta:local:*` storage for the main session records; these records are meant\n  to support future handoff and sharing.\n- No transcript copies on branch, commit, change, or pull request targets.\n  Future targets should reference durable project session keys.\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- What user-facing privacy controls should exist before shareable-ready\n  transcript contents are serialized or pushed?\n- Should capture default to `project` forever, or should future hooks add\n  explicit branch/change/commit relationship references?\n- What redaction policy is good enough before remote exchange?\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:59:07.788Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}